## Statistical Analysis and Machine Learning

The platform implements sophisticated statistical methodologies including Prophet-based anomaly detection, CUPED (Controlled-experiment Using Pre-Experiment Data) for variance reduction, and Non-Negative Matrix Factorization (NMF) for behavioral clustering in Personas charts.

**Experiment Analysis** utilizes mSPRT for sequential testing with configurable confidence intervals, mutual exclusion groups for preventing user overlap across experiments, and comprehensive lift calculations comparing absolute and relative improvements with statistical significance validation.

**AI-Powered Features** include transformer-based sequence models for predictive cohort generation, AutoML clustering for personalized recommendations, and conversational analytics through OpenAI LLM integration enabling natural language query capabilities.

## Compliance and Enterprise Capabilities

Amplitude maintains enterprise-grade security and compliance standards including SOC2 Type 2, GDPR, HIPAA, and CCPA compliance with comprehensive data processing agreements and privacy controls. The platform supports EU data residency, automated data deletion through DSAR APIs, and sophisticated consent management integration.

**Data Governance** features include comprehensive audit trails, granular permission systems with role-based access controls, data retention policies, and advanced user privacy controls including opt-out mechanisms and PII masking capabilities.

The platform serves organizations from startups to enterprise customers through tiered subscription models (Starter, Plus, Growth, Enterprise) with scalable pricing based on Monthly Tracked Users and feature access, supported by comprehensive professional services for implementation and migration from competing platforms including Adobe Analytics, Google Analytics, Mixpanel, and Segment.